<p><b>John Polkinghorne</b>, <a href="/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire" title="Order of the British Empire">KBE</a>, <a href="/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society" title="Fellow of the Royal Society" class="mw-redirect">FRS</a> (born October 16, 1930 in <a href="/wiki/Weston-super-Mare" title="Weston-super-Mare">Weston-super-Mare</a>, <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">England</a>) is a <a href="/wiki/UK" title="UK" class="mw-redirect">British</a> <a href="/wiki/Particle_physics" title="Particle physics">particle physicist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Theology" title="Theology">theologian</a>. He has written extensively on matters concerning science and faith (his most recent book being <a href="/wiki/Questions_of_Truth" title="Questions of Truth">Questions of Truth</a>), and was awarded the <a href="/wiki/Templeton_Prize" title="Templeton Prize">Templeton Prize</a> in 2002.</p>
