<p><a name="Secondary_sources" id="Secondary_sources"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=John_Polkinghorne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Secondary sources">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Secondary sources</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><i>God, Humanity and the Cosmos: A Textbook in Science and Religion</i> ed. by Dr. Christopher Southgate. T&amp;T Clark. <a href="http://www.meta-library.net/ghc-div/peaco1-body.html" class="external text" title="http://www.meta-library.net/ghc-div/peaco1-body.html" rel="nofollow">Relevant extracts</a>.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREF.5B.5BWolfhart_Pannenberg.5D.5D2009"><a href="/wiki/Wolfhart_Pannenberg" title="Wolfhart Pannenberg">Wolfhart Pannenberg</a> (2001). "Response to John Polkinghorne". <i>Zygon</i> <b>36</b> (4): 799–800. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1111%2F0591-2385.00398" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1111%2F0591-2385.00398" rel="nofollow">10.1111/0591-2385.00398</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Response+to+John+Polkinghorne&amp;rft.jtitle=Zygon&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BWolfhart+Pannenberg%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BWolfhart+Pannenberg%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.volume=36&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=799%E2%80%93800&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1111%2F0591-2385.00398&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Polkinghorne"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <a href="http://www.blackwell-synergy.com/doi/abs/10.1111/0591-2385.00398?cookieSet=1&amp;journalCode=zygo" class="external text" title="http://www.blackwell-synergy.com/doi/abs/10.1111/0591-2385.00398?cookieSet=1&amp;journalCode=zygo" rel="nofollow">abstract</a></li>
<li>Johannes Maria Steinke <i>John Polkinghorne – Konsonanz von Naturwissenschaft und Theologie</i> Vandenhoeck &amp; Ruprecht 2006 – a book investigating Polkinghorne's theory of consonance and analysing its philosophical background.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Taede_A._Smedes" title="Taede A. Smedes">Taede A. Smedes</a> <i>Chaos, Complexity, and God: Divine Action and Scientism</i> Louvain: Peeters 2004 – a theological investigation of Polkinghorne's (and <a href="/wiki/Arthur_Peacocke" title="Arthur Peacocke">Arthur Peacocke</a>'s) model of divine action.</li>
</ul>
